# Import Conventions

## Always use absolute imports
When importing modules or components in this project, always use absolute import paths rather than relative import paths.

### Example:
```python
# Correct (absolute imports)
from sim_local.agents.creative_director import CreativeDirectorAgent
from sim_local.tools.llm_tools import generate_scenario

# Incorrect (relative imports)
from ..agents.creative_director import CreativeDirectorAgent
from .tools.llm_tools import generate_scenario
```

This makes the codebase more maintainable and easier to refactor.
